Belgium already has high tax rates, but the government needs to raise
revenues to plug the budget deficit.

Mr di Rupo said: "The problem of social security will not be solved
only acting on the spending side and asking exclusively for an effort
from those who benefit from various social benefits".



<A HREF ="#HeadList">Back to Headline List</A><BR>
