Meanwhile, Nynex Mobile Communications Co. turned on its 200,000th customer

Meanwhile, Nynex Mobile Communications Co. turned on its 200,000th customer on
Dec. 8.  The honored customer, Barbara Moska, an associate vice-president for
Prudential-Bache Securities, was presented with a Nynex 832SR cellular
telephone.  Nynex reported that it has doubled its subscriber base in
"slightly less than 14 months," including more than 125,000 customers in the
N.Y. metropolitan area.  Nynex Mobile Communications Co. president Charles Many
commented that "the fact that our 200,000th customer is a woman reflects the
changes that the cellular market is experiencing as we head into the next
decade.  Five years ago, our customer base was roughly 4% women; now it's close
to 20%.  In fact, women make up the fastest growing segment of the cellular
telephone industry."



