January 1990

Audiovox Corp., 150 Marcus Blvd., Hauppauge, NY 11788, 516/231-7750, also

Audiovox Corp., 150 Marcus Blvd., Hauppauge, NY 11788, 516/231-7750, also
introduced multiple system registration in the software--not in the NAM--in all
of its models.  "You can register your phones in as many systems as you want,"
John Sunderland explained.  The feature is programmable from the handset.  The
user stores each phone number in a memory location as if it were a phone
number, including the SID (system ID number) and area code.  Also, the phones
come with 7-digit activation already built in, right from the factory, to make
selling the phones easier for retailers. "We provide the codes to the
carriers," Sunderland said.  "The phones cannot be unlocked until the sale is
approved.  They're secure on the shelf."



