It's not a cellphone, but in light of the fact that some cellular carriers

It's not a cellphone, but in light of the fact that some cellular carriers are
now using photos of Don Adams, who played Maxwell Smart in the "Get Smart" TV
series, which made the shoe phone famous, we couldn't help being amused by "The
Sneaker Phone," a home phone built into a shoe, marketed by Kinetic Marketing
Inc., 1133 Broadway, Room 210, New York, NY 10010, 212/620-0600.  The phone
retails for $24.95.  "For mobile use, be sure to bring a long cord," company
veep Charles Beyda said.  The play-on-words possibilities are endless.  "For
communications on the go," "for that long mile" or "for the sole-filled
conversations in your life" are just a few.  But we'd better stop before we put
our foot in our mouth (which might be an improvement).



